title: Has the gulf between the generations ever been so vast?
text: show ad Has the gulf between the generations ever been so vast? Victoria, 21, has slept with nine men and boasted about it on TV. At the same age, her granny was a mother, married to the man she's now spent 51 years with Joyce Thornton met her husband at 16, was engaged by 18, and married by 20 Her granddaughter Victoria Cobbold is 21 but shows no sign of settling down In a unique TV experiment, they are forced to share a villa for a month on holiday
